{"id":3981,"date":"2015-12-21T18:06:27","date_gmt":"2015-12-22T01:06:27","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/?p=3981"},"modified":"2019-04-16T13:11:50","modified_gmt":"2019-04-16T19:11:50","slug":"succulent-boutonniere-ideas-for-your-diy-wedding","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/succulent-boutonniere-ideas-for-your-diy-wedding\/","title":{"rendered":"How to Make Succulent Boutonnieres for Your DIY Wedding"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-0 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-1\"><p><em>Creating a boutonniere out of succulents is so simple and so unique! Learn how to make your own with this step-by-step guide!<\/em><\/p>\n<p>I always love looking through Pinterest and spotting succulents in bouquets and wedding\u00a0boutonnieres. I think succulents would also make for a very unique prom boutonniere as well!<\/p>\n<p>I attempted making some boutonnieres a while ago and the result was not so pretty. So, I asked Erin if she would show me how to make boutonnieres with succulents.<\/p>\n<p>Making boutonnieres\u00a0is a lot simpler than I thought and I thought her combinations of plants were really pretty! If you are looking to make your own boutonnieres for your wedding or prom, take a look at the tutorial below!<\/p>\n<p>You can <a href=\"https:\/\/thesucculentsource.com\/collections\/succulent-cuttings?aff=20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">purchase cuttings<\/a> for them here. If you're looking for other succulents for your wedding you'll love <a href=\"https:\/\/thesucculentsource.com\/?aff=20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">The Succulent Source<\/a>!<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-5911 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-boutonnieres-are-a-great-touch-for-any-wedding-and-are-simple-to-make.jpg\" alt=\"Succulent boutonniere's are a great touch for any wedding and are simple to make!\" width=\"735\" height=\"1103\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-boutonnieres-are-a-great-touch-for-any-wedding-and-are-simple-to-make-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-boutonnieres-are-a-great-touch-for-any-wedding-and-are-simple-to-make-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-boutonnieres-are-a-great-touch-for-any-wedding-and-are-simple-to-make.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>First off, here are the supplies you\u2019ll need:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=boutonnieres_supplies&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F226833783%2F20-succulent-cuttings-perfect-for-wall%3Fref%3Dshop_home_active_4\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Succulent cuttings<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"http:\/\/amzn.to\/2iSdmhg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Scissors<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B001K7QAYM\/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B001K7QAYM&linkCode=as2&tag=cassituttlpho-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Wire<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B002HRAEHS\/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B002HRAEHS&linkCode=as2&tag=cassituttlpho-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Wire cutters<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B007RIJ2L6\/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B007RIJ2L6&linkCode=as2&tag=cassituttlpho-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Floral tape<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B0057Y0536\/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B0057Y0536&linkCode=as2&tag=cassituttlpho-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Ribbon<\/a><\/li>\n<li>A <a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B00566E720\/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B00566E720&linkCode=as2&tag=cassituttlpho-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">boutonniere pin<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>The first thing you\u2019ll want to do is decide what succulents you\u2019ll want to pair together. One thing I love about Erin\u2019s work is her combination of colors and textures. Once you know what you want together, you\u2019ll start adding the wire.<\/p>\n<p>Depending on the succulent you are using, you may need to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/toolsas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">cut<\/a> off the roots.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-3988\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Cut-off-Roots-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"Cut off Roots - How to Make a Succulent Boutonniere - www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Since succulents don\u2019t have a long stem you need to add wire to create a \u201cstem\u201d. To do this, insert a piece of wire in the base of the succulent and push it through until the halfway point.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-3982\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Place-Wire-through-Succulent-Stem-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"Place Wire through Succulent Stem - How to Make a Succulent Boutonniere - www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Here is another way you can add the wire to the stem:<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-3985\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Another-Way-to-Wrap-Wire-for-Stem-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"Another Way to Wrap Wire for Stem - How to Make a Succulent Boutonniere - www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Then you\u2019ll fold the wire down to form the base for the \u201cstem\u201d.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-3983\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Fold-Down-Wire-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"Fold Down Wire - How to Make a Succulent Boutonniere - www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Next, you\u2019ll take a piece of floral tape and wrap the actual stem of the succulent all the way down to the bottom of the wire.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-3987\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Wrap-Floral-Tape-Around-Wire-to-Create-Stem-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"Wrap Floral Tape Around Wire to Create Stem - How to Make a Succulent Boutonniere - www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The nice thing about having a wire stem is you can easily bend the head of the succulent to make it face whatever way you want. After\u00a0you've\u00a0created a stem for all the succulents you are going to use you can start putting the boutonniere together. Start by wrapping two of the succulents together.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-3989\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Place-Two-Cuttings-Next-to-Each-Other-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x750.jpg\" alt=\"Place Two Cuttings Next to Each Other - How to Make a Succulent Boutonniere - www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Place-Two-Cuttings-Next-to-Each-Other-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Place-Two-Cuttings-Next-to-Each-Other-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Place-Two-Cuttings-Next-to-Each-Other-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-3984\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Wrap-Cuttings-Together-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"Wrap Cuttings Together - How to Make a Succulent Boutonniere - www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Add the third succulent and use floral tape to attach all the stems together.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Wrap-Floral-Tape-Around-Cuttings-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"Wrap Floral Tape Around Cuttings - How to Make a Succulent Boutonniere - www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Once this is done, you can add ribbon and a pin and now\u00a0you've\u00a0completed your succulent boutonniere!\u00a0I also put together a video of her making one of the boutonnieres so you can see this process in action.<\/p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/juMw1fI13ZI\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"><\/iframe><\/p>\n<p>I love how these turned out. We had a nice variety of plants from <a href=\"http:\/\/gosucculent.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Daniel\u2019s Specialty Nursery<\/a> that gave these a unique look. The Kalanchoe delagoensis\u00a0were especially fun because they are so unique (the main succulent in focus below).<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7271\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Wow-This-succulent-boutonniere-is-awesome-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Wow! This succulent boutonniere is awesome!\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7270\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/This-succulent-boutonniere-is-gorgeous-and-the-colors-are-so-unique-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"This succulent boutonniere is gorgeous and the colors are so unique!\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7272\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/I-love-all-the-bright-colors-in-this-succulent-boutonniere-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"I love all the bright colors in this succulent boutonniere!\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<p>If\u00a0you've\u00a0used succulents for your wedding or event I\u2019d love to see! Feel free to leave a comment linking to photos or send me an email! Also, be sure to stop by and see more of Erin\u2019s beautiful arrangements at Floral Design by Erin.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-3995 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Boutonnieres-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_.jpg\" alt=\"Succulent Boutonnieres - How to Make a Succulent Boutonniere - www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"240\" height=\"721\" \/><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3996 alignnone\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Boutonniere-Ideas-How-to-Make-a-Succulent-Boutonniere-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_.jpg\" alt=\"Succulent Boutonniere Ideas - How to Make a Succulent Boutonniere - www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"240\" height=\"721\" \/><\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-2 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-1 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;